<description><![CDATA[<p>I just ran across <a href="http://alternet.org/mediaculture/31753/">this article on Alternet</a> a minute ago and felt I needed to share. It talks about how telecommunications and cable companies are working to not only monitor and track everything we do online, but also charge us exorbitant fees for surfing and sending emails. As the article asks, is this the end of the internet as we know it?</p>]]></description>
